Command:
  make -j1 verify_separated_pole_turan_ect

Strict build:
  g++ -O2 -std=c++20 -Wall -Wextra -Wpedantic -Wconversion \
    -Wsign-conversion -Wshadow -Werror \
    verify_separated_pole_turan_ect.cpp -o verify_separated_pole_turan_ect

Command:
  /usr/bin/time -f 'elapsed=%e maxrss=%MKB' \
    ./verify_separated_pole_turan_ect 9 10 16

Output:
  SEPARATED_POLE_ECT maximum_separation=9 maximum_power=10 \
  maximum_degree=16 coefficient_checks=77518 \
  determinant_checks=72898 wronskian_checks=1532426 result=PASS
  elapsed=75.88 maxrss=3072KB

Scope:
  Every check is exact integer arithmetic.  The coefficient checks evaluate
  the rational series directly.  The determinant checks independently use
  Bareiss elimination on the generalized Vandermonde matrix in Lemma 22H3S.
  The Wronskian checks compare the direct derivative determinant with
  formula (P22.5zz53) and verify strict positivity.  These bounded checks
  audit the identities; the all-parameter conclusion is supplied by the
  Chebyshev-system proof, not by extrapolation.
